President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring November 20-26, 2016, as National Family Week in the United States. In the proclamation, he highlights the importance of families in society and expresses a commitment to ensuring that every family has a fair chance at success. He discusses various efforts his administration has made to strengthen families, including providing affordable healthcare through the Affordable Care Act, advocating for paid family and sick leave, fair work schedules, equal pay for women, and raising the federal minimum wage. He also recognizes the diversity of American families, including adoptive and foster families, military families, and same-sex couples. The proclamation calls on all states, communities, and individuals to observe National Family Week with appropriate ceremonies and activities to honor families.